article.headline: W. Michigan 89, Valparaiso 80, OT
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Joe Reitz scored eight of his game-high 24 points in overtime, leading Western Michigan to an 89-80 win over Valparaiso in an ESPNU BracketBuster matchup Saturday. Reitz survived foul trouble to score 16 points in the second half and overtime combined. The junior center hit all five shots he took and converted 14-of-18 free throws as the Broncos (12-14) overcame a seven-point deficit in the final four minutes of regulation. Reitz, who was on the bench with his third foul 1:30 into the second half, also had a game-high 10 rebounds. Urule Igbavboa scored a career-high 21 points and had nine rebounds for Valparaiso (14-14), but missed a shot in the final minute of regulation and fouled out in overtime. Samuel Haanpaa added 19, hitting a game-high four 3-pointers. Western Michigan tied a University Arena record by converting 36 free throws. The Broncos attempted 41. The teams combined for 65 free throws and 53 fouls. The lead changed 17 times between the regional rivals, but a lay-in basket by Reitz with 3:09 left in overtime gave the Broncos the lead for good. That began a 10-0 run by Western Michigan as the Crusaders missed 4-of-6 shots in the extra period and turned the ball over three times. Including regulation, Valparaiso scored three baskets in the last 8:30 and was outscored 24-8. Shawntes Gary added 19 points for Western Michigan, which reached a season high in points scored. David Kool and Derek Fracalossi each scored 16. Jarryd Loyd came off the bench to score 14 for the Crusaders, tying a career high.
